    "text": "Your resting heart rate is 62 bpm as of this morning — essentially on top of your 30-day average resting heart rate of 61.8 bpm, so nothing unusual is happening. Resting heart rate is how fast your heart beats when you're completely at rest; your device reads it overnight, when it's steadiest. One mix-up worth avoiding: your respiratory rate is 16.5 breaths per minute — that's a breathing measure that sits next to the heart numbers in most apps, not a pulse reading. With today's value within a beat of baseline and your 7-day average resting heart rate at 62 bpm, this is a stable, unremarkable reading — exactly what you want to see.",
